(candidates whose repository label matches the predicted query class. If fewer than five such ) Tj
T*
(candidates are available, the method fills the remaining slots by raw distance.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the semantic layer cannot be trained, the method does not fall back to raw Euclidean top-5. ) Tj
T*
(Instead, it uses standardized Euclidean distance:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(z_i = frac{x_i-mu_i}{sigma_i}, qquad) Tj
T*
(d_z\(q,r\)=lVert z_q-z_rrVert_2^2.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository mean and standard deviation are computed once in Retrieval.__init__. Exact ) Tj
T*
(repository self-queries always keep the self row in the first slot, while the remaining slots ) Tj
T*
(come from the semantic or standardized ranking rather than a raw-baseline copy. The method also ) Tj
T*
(computes the best augmented match under eight one-pixel shifts, seven non-identity D4 ) Tj
T*
(rotations/reflections, and a 3x3 mean-blurred repository channel.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The final output may replace the fifth slot by the best augmented candidate if the augmented ) Tj
T*
(distance is no larger than the raw fifth-neighbor distance:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(frac{d_{text{aug}}\(q,r^*\)}{d_{text{raw-5}}\(q\)} le 1.0.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Blur is handled more conservatively by comparing against the raw top-1 distance, because blurred) Tj
T*
( images tend to be close to many vectors in absolute distance. Every output row is guaranteed to) Tj
T*
( contain five distinct valid row indices.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pseudo-code:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  store repository features, row norms, and optional repository labels) Tj
T*
(  if classification training data is available:) Tj
T*
(      train an ExtraTrees / HGB / MLP semantic ensemble) Tj
T*
(  compute repository mean/std and standardized repository features) Tj
T*
(  set a soft deadline below the 600 second task limit) Tj
T*
(  for each query chunk:) Tj
T*
(      compute raw squared Euclidean distances) Tj
T*
(      predict query class probabilities with the semantic ensemble if available) Tj
T*
(      compute standardized squared Euclidean distances) Tj
T*
(      detect exact repository self-query if present) Tj
T*
(      compute minimum distance over shift transforms) Tj
T*
(      compute minimum distance over D4 transforms) Tj
T*
(      compute blur-channel distance) Tj
T*
(      if semantic predictions are available:) Tj
T*
(          choose top-5 by same-predicted-class priority within raw top-200) Tj
T*
(      otherwise:) Tj
T*
(          start from standardized top-5) Tj
T*
(      if query is an exact repository row:) Tj
T*
(          keep self row in slot 0 and use non-self semantic/standardized neighbors) Tj
T*
(      replace at most the fifth slot by the best eligible augmented match) Tj
T*
(      if remaining time becomes risky:) Tj
T*
(          use standardized top-5 fallback for the remaining query chunks) Tj
T*
(      return repository row indices) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The retrieval pass remains \(O\(qnd\)\) up to a small constant from the augmentation bank, where \(q\)) Tj
T*
( is the number of queries, \(n\) is repository size, and \(d=256\). Semantic model training happens ) Tj
T*
(once in the constructor, which matches the OJ protocol that constructs each class only once.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Experiments) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For exact self-query evaluation, I check whether the original repository row is recovered in the) Tj
T*
( top-5. Exact self recall is already saturated by raw Euclidean search, so matching 1.0 is a ) Tj
T*
ET
